metadata.education: Applied university (HBO in Dutch)/ University bachelor

survey.automatic_detection_helpful_explanation: to me it seemed that the automatic detection often indicated the first block of a changing pattern, which is not an anomaly. in other cases it was helpful. i would say by feeling it indicated correctly about 50% of the time.
survey.history_helpful_explanation: especially in the long patterns it seemed easier to spot anomalies.
survey.issues_or_interruptions: I don't think I did. one thing I noticed during the tasks: the row I had the mouse pointer on started lagging behind the other rows, but when I moved the mouse pointer the row quickly 'caught up' to the other rows to be 'in sync' again. I don't know if this was intentional but it did not bother me.
